    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Showing current git branch name in your bash prompt]]></title>
    <link href="http://solidfoxrock.github.io/blog/2014/05/18/showing-current-git-branch-name-in-your-bash-prompt/"/>
    <updated>2014-05-18T14:40:21+07:00</updated>
    <id>http://solidfoxrock.github.io/blog/2014/05/18/showing-current-git-branch-name-in-your-bash-prompt</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Here is my prompt which I think very nice:</p>

<p><img src="http://solidfoxrock.github.io/images/myprompt.png" alt="Alt image" /></p>

<p>To have this prompt you need the following into your <code>~/.bash_profile</code>:</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nv">COLORWHITE</span><span class="o">=</span>&amp;lsquo;<span class="o">[</span><span class="se">\0</span>33<span class="o">[</span>00m<span class="o">]</span>&amp;rsquo;
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">COLORGREEN</span><span class="o">=</span>&amp;lsquo;<span class="o">[</span><span class="se">\0</span>33<span class="o">[</span>01;32m<span class="o">]</span>&amp;rsquo;
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">COLORPINK</span><span class="o">=</span>&amp;lsquo;<span class="o">[</span><span class="se">\0</span>33<span class="o">[</span>01m<span class="o">]</span>&amp;rsquo;
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">COLORLAVENDER</span><span class="o">=</span>&amp;lsquo;<span class="o">[</span><span class="se">\0</span>33<span class="o">[</span>01;36m<span class="o">]</span>&amp;rsquo;
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">COLORYELLOW</span><span class="o">=</span>&amp;lsquo;<span class="o">[</span><span class="se">\0</span>33<span class="o">[</span>01;33m<span class="o">]</span>&amp;rsquo;
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">export </span><span class="nv">GIT_PS1_SHOWDIRTYSTATE</span><span class="o">=</span>1
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">export </span><span class="nv">PS1</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nv">$COLORGREEN</span><span class="s1">&#39;\u@\h&#39;</span><span class="nv">$COLORWHITE</span><span class="s1">&#39;[&amp;lsquo;$COLORPINK&amp;rsquo;\t&#39;</span><span class="nv">$COLORWHITE</span><span class="s1">&#39;]:&amp;lsquo;$COLORLAVENDER&amp;rsquo;\w&#39;</span><span class="nv">$COLORYELLOW</span><span class="err">&#39;</span><span class="k">$(</span>__git_ps1<span class="k">)</span>&amp;lsquo;<span class="nv">$COLORWHITE</span>&amp;rsquo;<span class="se">\n\$</span> &amp;lsquo;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>If opening a new console gives you the error <code>bash: __git_ps1: command not found</code>, then you need to do these extra steps:</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'>curl -sL -o ~/.git-prompt.sh &lt;a <span class="nv">href</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;https://raw.github.com/git/git/master/contrib/completion/git-prompt.sh&quot;</span>&gt;https://raw.github.com/git/git/master/contrib/completion/git-prompt.sh&lt;/a&gt;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>Add the following line into your <code>~/.bash_profile</code>, before the line <code>export PS1</code>:</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nb">source</span> ~/.git-prompt.sh
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>Thanks to <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/a/12871094/195929">Mark Longair&rsquo;s answer</a> on StackOverflow</p>
]]></content>
